install config
install mysql2
install inquirer

prompt questions: --promptUser()
    -view all departments,  --viewDept()
        presents tables with department names and department ids

    -view all roles, --viewRoles()
        presents table with job title, role id, department of that role id
        salary for that role

    -view all employees, --viewEmployees()
        presents table with employee data, employee ids, first names, last names, job titles, departments, salaries, and managers that the employees report to

    -add a department, --addDept()
        asked to enter name of department and that department is
        added to the database

    -add a role, --addRole()
        prompted to entername, salary and department of that role, 
        and that role is added to the database

    -add an employee, --addEmployee()
        prompted to enter firstname, lastname, role, manager, and
        that employee is added to the database

    -and update an employee role --updateRole()
        prompted to select and employee and update their new role and 
        this information is updated in the database


GIVEN a command-line application that accepts user input
WHEN I start the application
THEN I am presented with the following options: view all departments, view all roles, view all employees, add a department, add a role, add an employee, and update an employee role
WHEN I choose to view all departments
THEN I am presented with a formatted table showing department names and department ids
WHEN I choose to view all roles
THEN I am presented with the job title, role id, the department that role belongs to, and the salary for that role
WHEN I choose to view all employees
THEN I am presented with a formatted table showing employee data, including employee ids, first names, last names, job titles, departments, salaries, and managers that the employees report to
WHEN I choose to add a department
THEN I am prompted to enter the name of the department and that department is added to the database
WHEN I choose to add a role
THEN I am prompted to enter the name, salary, and department for the role and that role is added to the database
WHEN I choose to add an employee
THEN I am prompted to enter the employeeâ€™s first name, last name, role, and manager, and that employee is added to the database
WHEN I choose to update an employee role
THEN I am prompted to select an employee to update and their new role and this information is updated in the database






